Special Anti-Robbery Squad (SARS) team, at the weekend, rescued four kidnapped persons, including a professor, from their abductors. Prof. Ekezie Christopher, 72, Aminu Ibrahim, 55, Friday Udoh, 33, and Onyekachi Nwibe, 29, were said to be rescued unhurt when the operatives engaged the kidnappers in a shootout in the forest. Police spokesman Orlando Ikeokwu confirmed the incident. Police in Delta State yesterday confirmed the release of a medical doctor Wisdom Iboyitete kidnapped in Burutu council area of the state last week Sunday.